## What is a DateTime variable?

The DateTime (System.dateTime) enables you to store information about the date and time in variables.

    -This variable can be found in Browse and Select a .Net system, under the namespace System.DateTime.

The reason why we would use DateTime variable is to include appending documents and or perform time span calculations. 

---

## What are some business scenarios in which DateTime would be used?

Working with time-sensitive documents such as invoices in scenarios where:

    *the time format varies throughout the process.

    *a specific amount of time needs to be added or subtracted while processing documents.
